{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"API request always contains the full taxonomy label list.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: a pure unit test of prompt-builder logic can miss wiring bugs where handler/service omits labels before calling the API client. REAL-INFRA: no OS/network is required if we use an in-process fake client. MOCK-HIDE: mocking too low (single function) can hide module handoff failures. LLM-DEP: not dependent on model judgment.","test_description":"Wire the classifier module with a fake API transport that records outbound payloads. Call classify() with sample docs and assert every request contains exactly the configured taxonomy labels (no missing/extra labels) at the boundary passed to the transport.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Out-of-taxonomy API label is mapped to \"unknown\".","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: unit-testing only a mapper function can miss how raw API responses are parsed and validated in the module path. REAL-INFRA: can be tested locally with a fake API response. MOCK-HIDE: over-mocking internals may bypass the real response-handling path. LLM-DEP: no real model quality requirement.","test_description":"Run classifier with a fake API client returning an invalid label (e.g., \"medical\"). Assert classify() returns \"unknown\" and never exposes the raw invalid label to callers.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Same document yields same classification across repeated calls.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness depends on real model output stability; a mock cannot reveal true nondeterminism/drift. MOCK-HIDE: deterministic stubs will always pass and hide real variance. MULTI-STEP: this is repeated single-step calls, not a multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Against the real AI classification endpoint and production prompt/settings, classify the same document N times (e.g., 50-100) over separate calls; fail if returned labels are not identical (or exceed a strict variance threshold if spec allows).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Token usage for a typical document stays within configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-HIDE: mocked token counters can miss mismatch with provider token accounting and real request framing. REAL-INFRA: requires real API usage metrics (or real tokenizer/runtime path) to catch true cost failures. LLM-DEP: this is primarily infrastructure/accounting, not model judgment quality.","test_description":"Send representative documents through the real API path in a non-prod project, capture provider-reported token usage per call, and assert usage <= configured budget; include boundary-size docs near the expected limit.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.35,"System":0.45,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"On rate-limit signal, module waits and retries instead of surfacing error immediately.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: unit tests of backoff math alone can miss retry orchestration between classifier, client wrapper, and error handling. REAL-INFRA: no real network required if a controllable fake client emits rate-limit errors and then success. MOCK-HIDE: overly coarse mocks may skip timing/retry path entirely.","test_description":"Use a fake API client scripted to return rate-limit error on first call and success on second, with a controllable clock/sleeper. Assert classifier performs a delayed retry (with expected backoff behavior) and eventually returns a label, not an error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
